laboratory_examinations.findings: Total plasma tricyclic antidepressant level was 805 ng/ml (imipramine = 193, desipramine = 612), which is far above the usual therapeutic range of 180-250 ng/ml.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: A repeat sample drawn on March 9 revealed a total plasma tricyclic level of 696 ng/ml (imipramine = 174, desipramine = 522). On March 20, the total plasma tricyclic level was 252 ng/ml (imipramine = 51, desipramine = 201). On March 31, the total plasma tricyclic level had fallen to 143 ng/ml (imipramine = 23, desipramine = 120). On May 2, the plasma tricyclic level was 307 ng/ml (imipramine = 85, desipramine = 222).
